00:28:07.527 --> 00:28:11.160
AUDIENCE: I had a quick
comment about strategic voting,

00:28:11.160 --> 00:28:12.990
because it came up.

00:28:12.990 --> 00:28:17.040
So everyone mentioned that
for no single member district

00:28:17.040 --> 00:28:18.185
is it--

00:28:18.185 --> 00:28:20.310
there's no voting system
that completely eliminates

00:28:20.310 --> 00:28:23.220
strategic voting, even
in instant runoff,

00:28:23.220 --> 00:28:26.370
because of that situation
where who your first choice is

00:28:26.370 --> 00:28:29.790
matters, in terms of whether
a candidate who was otherwise

00:28:29.790 --> 00:28:32.370
widely acceptable can get
eliminated in the first round.

00:28:32.370 --> 00:28:36.960
There is some incentive
to strategically vote

00:28:36.960 --> 00:28:38.550
for who your first
choice is, even

00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:41.140
with instant runoff voting.

00:28:41.140 --> 00:28:45.360
There's analysis I saw
which showed ratings,

00:28:45.360 --> 00:28:50.640
or approval voting
does have less ability

00:28:50.640 --> 00:28:52.530
to vote strategically,
and certainly even

00:28:52.530 --> 00:28:57.420
instant runoff voting still is
much lower than single-member.

00:28:57.420 --> 00:29:00.090
But I believe from
what I've read,

00:29:00.090 --> 00:29:03.062
if you have multi-member
districts, that largely gets

00:29:03.062 --> 00:29:04.270
[INAUDIBLE] strategic voting.

00:29:04.270 --> 00:29:06.300
So I wasn't sure if you
had thoughts on that.

00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:07.050
BRIAN OLSON: Yeah.

00:29:07.050 --> 00:29:09.430
That gets into proportional
representation.

00:29:09.430 --> 00:29:13.140
So if you're electing five
or more people at once,

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:15.810
then you want to vote
for who you really want,

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:20.340
and you're more
likely to get them,

00:29:20.340 --> 00:29:23.850
because you will be voting
as part of some coalition,

00:29:23.850 --> 00:29:24.750
most likely.

00:29:24.750 --> 00:29:28.320
You will be voting with the
Dems or Greens or Libertarians

00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:36.500
or Republicans or the Nature
Conservancy or the gun lobby.

00:29:36.500 --> 00:29:39.250
You will be voting with
some group on the issue,

00:29:39.250 --> 00:29:42.510
and so you will get
something, most likely,

00:29:42.510 --> 00:29:44.910
in a proportional
representation scheme.

00:29:44.910 --> 00:29:51.780
So it's a pressure release
valve for the pressure

00:29:51.780 --> 00:29:53.130
of electing one person.

00:29:55.947 --> 00:29:58.030
AUDIENCE: Thanks for the
talk and for all the work

00:29:58.030 --> 00:29:59.470
you're doing.

